    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Lower Township, which includes Villas, was incorporated in 1798 and contains historic towns like Cold Spring and Erma.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://townshipoflower.org/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Villas sits in a county whose history spans more than 300 years, from Lenni Lenape to pirate legends and the Underground Railroad.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4,
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://capemaycountynj.gov/928/Visit-The-Jersey-Cape"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Victorian architecture, a hallmark of Cape May County, is preserved throughout the region, including the streets of Villas.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        7
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://capemaycountynj.gov/928/Visit-The-Jersey-Cape"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "Route 9, the historic stage‑coach road from Philadelphia, cuts through the county and echoes its early transportation heritage.",
